11/06/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis met with NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer on Thursday (10 June) to discuss preparations for the Summer Olympics. At issue was Greece's request for NATO assistance in preventing terrorist attacks. The two officials also discussed the upcoming NATO summit in Istanbul and agreed that the Euro-Atlantic aspirations of Southeast European states are strengthening regional security. (MPA, Makfax - 10/06/04)
